         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>21st Century Schools Technical Advisor MIM</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>C188/2017/2018</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="71530000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Welsh Government is seeking to appoint a Technical Advisor for the Mutual Investment Model element of the 21<FT TYPE="SUP">st</FT> Century Schools and Education Programme: Band B. The Mutual investment Model is a Public Private Partnership. The Welsh Government recognises that the selection of the right adviser teams is critical to the success of Band B of its 21<FT TYPE="SUP">st</FT> Century Schools and Education Programme. The role of the Technical Adviser is a key one for the Welsh Government in its delivery of Mutual Investment Model (MIM) projects in Band B the theoretical technical knowledge required from the successful candidate needs to be complemented with practical deal-making experience of recent public sector education infrastructure programmes.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">5000000</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71530000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71311300"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71315200"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="79415200"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71240000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71311000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71313000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="79410000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>For the MIM Projects in Band B, the Technical Adviser, as our infrastructure and Public Private Partnership (PPP)consultants, will join a.</P>
                  <P>Team of other specialist advisers including financial and legal. We do not require the Technical Adviser to act as lead adviser, nor do we.</P>
                  <P>Require the Technical Adviser to act as project manager for Band B. However, the Technical Adviser will be required to manage the.</P>
                  <P>Specialist advisers in its supply chain as Welsh Government is expecting a single point of contact from its Technical Advisory team.</P>
                  <P>Packages of Work: Welsh Government – Mutual Investment Model:</P>
                  <P>— production of Standard Documents for the construction of Schools and Colleges,</P>
                  <P>— production of Standard specifications,</P>
                  <P>— production of facilities specifications,</P>
                  <P>— development of the Tranches,</P>
                  <P>— development of Authority documents for Bidding,</P>
                  <P>— providing advise on BREEAM, Building regulations, planning,</P>
                  <P>— drafting survey specifications,</P>
                  <P>— development of life cycle and maintenance services,</P>
                  <P>— evaluation Criteria for technical elements,</P>
                  <P>— support during technical elements of Competitive Dialogue,</P>
                  <P>— support in Producing Business Case for Tranches.</P>
                  <P>The Technical Adviser will be required to provide the Services from Wales. Frequent and regular face to face meetings will be required.</P>
                  <P>Both in Cardiff and at the MIM authorities. Travel will be required to these locations.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
